<subSubSection id="6DC56513FFFAFFF7E292A37CCCE174BE" lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="25603698FFFAFFF6E292A37CCB557582" blockId="20.[151,1437,282,489]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFAFFF6E292A37CCF05755E" bold="true" box="[151,325,282,308]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Type material.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFFAFFF6E349A37CCFF4755E" box="[332,436,282,308]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Holotype</typeStatus>
MCZ 4499 (Scudder’s no. 3350), collected by Henry Wickham. A nearly compete specimen in dorsal aspect, with distal portions of wings not preserved. Verbatim label data [typed and handwritten]: “(1) “Mus. Comp. Zoöl. Cambridge, Mass. / No. 4499 / Paleochrysa 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFAFFF6E175A305CA237516" authority="Cock." authorityName="Cock." box="[880,1123,354,381]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wickhami">
[
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFAFFF6E17FA305CDD97516" box="[890,921,355,380]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">sic</emphasis>
] wickhami Cock.
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFFAFFF6E67FA304CAA27516" box="[1146,1250,354,380]" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Holotype</typeStatus>
/ H.F. Wickham coll. Florissant”; (2) [handwritten]: “4499 type Paleochrysa 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFAFFF6E141A3E1CA7875CA" authority="Cock." authorityName="Cock." box="[836,1080,390,417]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Lithochrysa" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wickhami">
[
<emphasis id="17ABEA8AFFFAFFF6E148A3E1CD2C75CA" box="[845,876,391,416]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">sic</emphasis>
] wickhami Cock.
</taxonomicName>
/ Florissant / 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFAFFF6E6D2A3E0CB1C75CA" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[1239,1372,390,416]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Neuroptera</taxonomicName>
”. The specimen has black ink writing on the rock that says “4499”, and a red paper label glued to the rock that says “ 
<typeStatus id="FA64883AFFFAFFF6E76BA3CCCEA37582" pageId="20" pageNumber="321">Holotype</typeStatus>
”. A paper label glued to the reverse of the rock says: “ 
<taxonomicName id="E2DF4D1BFFFAFFF6E13BA3A8CD957582" box="[830,981,462,488]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Palaeochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Palaeochrysa</taxonomicName>
/ wickhami / Ckll. / TYPE.”
</paragraph>
<caption id="71A06610FFFAFFF6E292A5FCCD127390" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6522491" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6522491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6522491/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="321" startId="20.[151,250,1946,1970]" targetBox="[162,1426,512,1911]" targetPageId="20">
